KAET Channel 8 will offer the
first nationwide telecast of the
complete messiah" by Handel,
Thurs. Dec. "a, 1870 pm.


The "Messiah'' will be an
appropriate program for Christ
mas viewing and listening. Hailed
for more than two centuries as
masterpiece of religious art, the
oratorio tells the story of Jesus...
from the coming of the Messiah,
through the crucifixion, to the
promise of life after death.


The work is a dramatic set
ting drawn from scripture. The
story is recounted with musical
narratives, solo arias, and choral
anthems. ..the most famous of
which is the celebrated "Halle-
lujah" Chorus. ..all with orches-
trail accompa nimentS.

More than 100000 auto tag
renewal notices are being mailed
to car owners this month by the
county auto license plate depart
ment.


Chief Clerk Bill Norris asks
all vehicle owners to carefully
examine their notice to make sure
it is accurate. =


Only mail applications will be
processed in December.


Beginning Jan. 4 applications
will be accepted over-the-coun-
ter at auto license headquarters,
40O5 N. 5lst Ave., Phoenix, and
1924 w. 4th ST., Mesa. Mail and
over-the-counter applications
will continue to be accepted
through Jan. 81 without a pen
atty charge.


Norris pointed out that fees
on many older model vehicles
will be slightly higher this year
due to new state law that be-
came effective July 18th which
raised registration fees from
81 to $6.25 on all vehicles. This
will raise the penalty fee and
cost of late registrations from
So to $3.50.


Widows and veterans must sign
for and obtain their exemption
slips from the county assessors
office after Jan. A before spply-
ing for exemptions on their auto
tags.


A single tab will be issued
for proof of 1865 registration.
This should be placed in the upper,
right hand corner of the rear
license plate.

The public is invited to the
affair, which will take place at
8 IN. Unitarian Church of Phoe-
nix, 4O27 East Lincoln Drive.


The Rev. L. J.. Smallsreed, <
pastor of the Scottsdale Con-
gregational United Church of
Christ, worked in Mississippi
last August in the project seek
ing to qualify Negroes to vote.

Well Folks,


Just wish that | could visit
all of you and personally ex-
tend to you, "a Merry Christ
mas and a Happy New Year"
Cant't possibly do that, so
I'll extend this invitation to
all COME BY REDDY'S
CORNER = and INSPECT OUR
VERY COMPLETE STOCKS.
We will do our best to help
you plan the best joyous Holt
day seasonl


Carolyn Jerry = Elnora


Maso and


AS Always,


Just FREDDY"
